https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/50mpg-geo-metro/6622485275.html,50MPG Geo Metro,1994 Geo Metro,Mount Vernon,1500,"1994 Geo Metro, 3 cylinder,
5 speed manual transmission. New tires less than 7,000 miles on them,
50 MPG, great little commuter car, runs and drives great, does not use, burn oil or smoke.

Dependable is an understatement since it's been in my family for 15 years. My dad owned it for 13 years and 2 years myself. If it wasn't dependable it would of left our family years ago. Only reason I'm selling is it's been just a back up car and my wife doesn't know how to drive a manual transmission so it doesn't get driven much except when ours or a family members car is in the shop it's the go to car.

Besides general maintenance not much has been done to it. I did put a new distributor cap and timing belt on it this year. Made it run even better. This car could easily drive another 100K Miles. The only damage to the body is behind the drivers door where a Prius backed into it and some rust under the door.

It's a basic bare bones car, manual windows, no A/C (came from the factory that way), no radio. Not flashy, but it makes up in dependability and a wonderful work car. Not an interstate car per say, but great highway/city car. Can cruise 60MPH all day. It can pay for itself just in the gas you'll save. I've never been able to put $20 in gas at fill up.
There's a reason why the Geo Metro is on the top ten list of most fuel efficient cars of all time. They don't make them like this anymore.

https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/2012-jaguar-xf-portfolio-v8/6625949853.html,2012 Jaguar XF Portfolio V8 26K Miles LOADED,2012 jaguar xf,"Marion, IL",23500,"You're looking at a beautiful British luxury sport sedan in the Jaguar XF. The 2012 model year was the last year that the 5.0L V8 was standard for the XF. If is the same engine used in the Jaguar XK GT car and will easily throw you back in the seats. This is the portfolio edition which includes a real leather dash, steering wheel, leather air conditioned and heated front seats, all leather back seats, headlights that turn with you as you drive, automatic headlight washers, suede leather headliner, sunroof, front and back bumper radar, rear view camera, GPS, internal hard drive for 10 CD's (it rips the CD's to the ""changer""), a loud and crisp stock radio, and every basic option beyond these. I purchased this car with under 8000 miles about 4 years ago. It has always been in the garage, driven in the rain less than 5 times, and never used as a daily driver. For what you get in this car for the price, I easily consider it an incredible value for the money. Especially since the first owner and now I have taken the bulk of the depreciation curve.

If you are new to Jaguar, don't be concerned by the brand and high maintenance costs. The engine has a lot of Ford pedigree and I get my oil changes at Marion Ford for about $125. You only need to change the oil once a year or at 10,000 miles. As you can see from the amount of miles on this car (about 26,500), I opted for the once per year oil change. I've had no problems with the car ever. It includes 2 Keys, one has wear and tear, the other looks like new.

Turn heads and enjoy top luxury with this gorgeous British sports sedan. With an original sticker price over $70,000, low miles, clean Car Fax (no accidents, no damage, maintenance records), it's a great value for the price!

Serious inquiries only. I prefer a local sale or one to an established car buying organization (VROOM, CARVANA, etc.). Contact me by phone only please to set up an appointment to see the car. I reserve the right to not allow you to test drive the car. Face to face meetings by private parties will happen at the Marion Police Department on Rt. 13 in Marion, IL in their established Craigslist meeting area. I do have a lien on the car so any transaction must occur during normal banking days / hours.

Super clean,2003 chevrolet silverado 2500hd 4x4,Eddyville Il,11500,"LB7 Duramax/Alison. Truck is super clean. My cousin bought it new in 03, I bought it from him in 08. Has had Rotella synthetic since 50K miles. I have all records from day one. Has 4"" exhaust, and firestone airbags. I installed a deep Alison trans pan and filter at 100K. All this was new at 187K. Rear U-Joints, Axle seals, Upgraded tie rods, wheel bearings, ball joints, upper control arms, pitman arm, idler arm, and braces for both, Bosch injectors, fuel pressure reg, adjusted valves, cat filter adapter. New t-stats at 212K the old ones stuck open. New tensioner, idler pulleys, and belt at 212K. Has a hypertech programmer thats been on it since 60K set on the 87hp setting and never changed. I change the fuel filter every oil change which I do when the computer oil life says 50%. I change the Alison spin on filter every 3rd oil change. I replaced the transfercase half with an aluminum one at 170K. I just had the stepper motors replaced on the gauges. Replace some brake lines, but not all. New Battery's feb of 16. Has the stock stereo and the cd player don't work. The drivers seat has one sewed spot. No other interior problems. Most of it looks new. It's due for a trans fluid replacement. I have 2 gallons of transynd that goes with the truck. I have the stock exhaust that goes with it. I have an aluminium louvered tailgate that goes with it. This truck has never gone into limp mode, NEVER. Every single thing works except cd player. The exterior has a dent, and some limb marks. The cab corners are rusted and the rockers are just starting. My cousin was in his 60's and I'm 47. I've never beat this truck. Its only been a tow/work truck. It has been very well maintained. I even keep the frame and rear axle painted. I'm getting another truck is the only reason for selling. If you want a great super clean truck come look at this one. I'm still driving it so mileage will go up slightly daily. 11,500 OBO Clear title in my name in my hand.

column1: https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/03-chevy-silverado-z71-for/6603026532.html,03 Chevy Silverado Z71 For Sale,2003 chevrolet 1500 silverado,Wood River,2100,"*** offer prices. I just put that price above ***
I'll give you the run down on this truck.

Transmission fluid was leaking and i had a hole in a manifold gasket whatever that is so I sent to Meineke and spent like $2,000. Then I get it back and the transmission was slipping so I got a used transmission from a junk yard and paid a mechanic labor to have it installed and apparently this ones junk to because it's still slipping. AAMCO transmissions said my $2,000 would of got the truck completely running but i didn't know about them. I did just drive it from Bunker hill to Wood River it runs smooth until you get up to about 45 - 50 mph. What I've had done this year to it is a new transfer case & fuel pump. I have receipts for those. I'm 99% sure I've got a lot more done to it as well as in replaced hoses and lines but I'd have to look at the receipts. I'm 100% done spending money on this truck. The mechanic says transmission is the main issue. I'm sure there's other areas that will need attention at some point. Engine seams good, no major noises or leaks.
* light rust over the passenger back wheel that can't really be seen.
* Rims are painted black by myself but they actually don't look that bad.
* Driver side and passenger front seats both have small rips as shown in the pictures.
* Rocker panels are rusted & there's a small rust hole in the bumper also shown in pictures.
* Bed of the truck does have a thin truck bed liner.
* A couple minor scratches and dings around the quarter panels of both sides.
If you have any questions, want more pictures or want to offer a price feel free to text me at",,fair,,4wd,gas,230000,black,,clean,automatic,truck

I have all the parts to rebuild it I just don't have time. It blew a head gasket. I have new timing belt, radiator, head gasket kit and new head bolts. Slight front fender damage from hitting deer. It's a great car and deserves to be back on the road. For the weekend mechanic this would be a great car and a bargain. The hard part is done. It has a 3.0L 24 valve twin dual over head cam. It is Hyundai's luxury model of that year. Looks like a Lincoln in the front and Similar to a Jaguar in the back. 5 speed automatic slap stick transmission. Super fun to drive. It also has new Windshield that was replaced before it was parked. If I can't sell it by Friday I will be forced to scrap it. I can get at least $220 from scrap and sell all the new parts and make more then what I'm asking. The car is to nice to scrap. Especially since I have all the parts. Except it will need two front tires (I used them for my s10) and a Battery. I will send pictures upon request. $500 or best offer. Clean title.",,,6 cylinders,,gas,,,,clean,automatic,

https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/datsun-521-pickup-truck/6622569138.html,Datsun 521 Pickup Truck,1971 Datsun 521,Carbondale,1200,"I have a Datsun 521 Truck with clean and clear title in my name. Had to move it out of the garage to work on my wagon. While I'd love to get this thing on the road but have too many projects. Has a L16 & 4 speed manual in it. I had it running earlier this year on a weber carb I borrowed from my 4 Door. Just needs someone with space and time.
Interior: Floor is pretty solid even up around the foot wells. Blue Vinyl bench seat is currently in the parts trucks cab.

Exterior: Worst part on this truck is the drivers side rocker, thankfully the rocker on the parts truck is there. Bed sides show dings from getting used as a truck should but no holes, bed floor is also fairly solid. Parts truck bed is in similar good condition.

Drivetrain: Engine fired up running off a motorcycle gastank & ran well after an oil change. Clutch & Brake lines are currently dry and need replaced so wasn't able to drive it around at all. Would recommend atleast a tune up & rebuilding the old hitachi carb that's on it as I've since removed the weber.

Mechanical: Brakes should be redone, I have new wheel cylinders & master cylinder for it. I was going to make new brake lines for it since it's a really simple system. Also cab and bed are off the parts frame so fabricating them would be pretty easy.
All in all it'd be a great project for somebody with the space/time. For me working out of an un-powered shed it's just too much. My loss your gain. Clean Illinois Title in my name in hand.
Come's with a complete parts truck & the parts to finish up the brakes and any other 521 parts I have if you offer close to asking price.
Also have a few other engine / transmissions I could sell along with the truck depending on offer (KA24DE/5speed & L20B/5speed)
I regularly check this email & can call or text if you provide a number

https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/chevy-powered-jeep-wrangler/6626429521.html,Chevy Powered Jeep Wrangler Rock Crawler,1995 Jeep Wrangler,"Raleigh, IL",14500,"As much as I hate to get rid of this thing, I have decided to move on to something else.  This started off as a 1995 Jeep Wrangler and has turned into what it is now.  I'll miss a lot of things, but I'll list out the majority.

388 stroker with Holley fuel injection (was a fresh motor when I got it a little over a year ago.  I do not have paperwork on the build, but it is a pretty healthy motor).  Has an MSD 6T, MSD Billit Distributor, MSD coil.  Rev limiter is setup on the Holley.

TH350 transmission with transmission cooler and fan.  This trans was just recently gone through at the end of last year.  I blew apart a sprag and put in a stock valve body rather than the manual valve body that was in it.  All seals and clutches were inspected and they were fairly new.
NP231C HD transfer case with advanced adapters kit
Ford 9"" rear.  4 linked on coils with a truss, spool, Moser shafts, 4.88 gears, and disk brake conversion
Front Dana 44, 3 linked on fox coil overs, Chromoly shafts, locker, new ring and pinion as of the end of last year (4.88's), warn premium hubs.
Allied 17x9.5 beadlocks with 38.5x13.50x17 boggers.  Tires are new, they have 1 wheeling trip and about 30 miles on them
Hydro assist steering, stock wrangler box, drilled out stock chevy pump.

I just got done redoing the front of the cage.  Originally it was designed without a top and doors in mind.  This winter I purchased a hard top, I already had the half doors, and purchased new glass for the windshield.  I bent new tubing and redesigned it so now the top fits, and doors fit.  The only thing that I do not have are the soft inserts.  You will need to find a set of TJ uppers and cut/reweld one of the rods and you'll be enclosed fully.

The Jeep drives down the road decently enough to drive it on occasion to town or to drive it to go wheel.  It's tagged and has insurance.   Currently the only thing the Jeep needs is a new 4wd linkage.  Long story short, the old one broke, a wrench welded to a piece of steel then bolted to the transfer case was used, and I bought a novak shifter and have issues with alignment so it doesn't work.  You can go back to the old setup, or make a new one, or get a cable setup.",,good,8 cylinders,4wd,gas,,white,,clean,automatic,offroad

https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/2006-bmw-m5-500-hp/6601976596.html,2006 BMW M5 500 H.P.,2006 BMW M5,Steeleville,9900,"I have for sale a 2006 BMW M5. Very rare car with only 83000 miles. I do not drive this car very much and have decided to sell it.  Please read the following before contacting me.  To make a long story short, about a year and a half ago, all of the warning lights came on on the dash and the diagnosis was the ECU motor.  I was told by BMW that if I replaced the ECU, then the car would have to be relearned to the new motor by a certified BWM dealer.  I replaced the ECU motor and took it to BMW and they hooked the computer up to it and after 6 or so hours, they said that their machine would not recognize the new ECU motor and therefore they said I would need to buy a new ECU motor from them.  At the time I did not wish to have them do this so the car has been setting in my garage ever since.  It runs good as is, but all of the warning lights are on.  Many BMW owners have this problem and never fix it.  The car is super fast and will be one of the most exhilarating machines you will ever drive.  I hope to have another one some day.  Call or text 6185five9877three.  I prefer text first.  Serious inquires only and please do not negotiate as this is my very bottom dollar.",,like new,10 cylinders,rwd,gas,,black,mid-size,clean,other,sedan

https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/1989-mazda-rx7-gxl/6629077623.html,1989 Mazda RX7 GXL,1989 mazda rx7,,2000,"Please read the whole description.  This is an ""as is "" sale.  This is a 1989 RX7 GXL.  All electrics work.  Has had seat belt recall done.  It is a drivable project.  Meaning it is drivable but does have issues you need to know about before buying.  Firstly the engine.  It is the original engine.  All 3 apex seals on both rotors have 85-89 psi which is in spec.  It does not use oil or coolant.  I use Idemitsu oil's for pre-mix and engine oil.  Original OMP still hooked up but I add some to the tank as well.  AC seems to blow cold.  All fluids are new.  Tires in great shape.  I have replaced all the vacuum hoses, rebuilt the throttle body and replaced the intake gaskets.   There is also alot more I have done to this in the last 3 years I have owned it.  I literally cannot rememeber them all.  It is an automatic but I do have a 5 speed and all parts needed to do the swap.  The automatic transmission works but I feel its putting a drag on the motor at idle in gear.  Which brings me to the issues.  While driving its fine, can set the cruise control and go anywhere, however at a stop in gear it wants to die.  This can be taken care of by going into neutral or using one foot on the brake and other on the gas.  Radio is missing but I have another.  Exhaust manifold leaks a little, but I have a Pacesetter header and a new O2 sensor to go with it.  There are several other new and used parts to go with it.  In the last few weeks I replaced the smog pump, which on the RX7 acutally operates important actuators on the intake to increase power and has a pipe that goes to the cat to prevent clogging due to the RX7s natural oil burning.  Now that the pump is new it is blowing out alot of stuff and smokes awhile.  It will do this until the system gets cleaned out.  Reason why I have not had a chance to drive it since is one of the heater hoses blew the day I installed the smog pump.  I have all new coolant hoses to go with it.  It will drive up on a trailer but until the heater hose is replaced it can not be driven.  I really like this car but would prefer the money right now.  The paint is not the best and there is some surface rust on the sunroof.  I may consider trades but it would have to be something classic/vintage and drivable, like a Jaguar, Mustang, etc.  Due to issues in the past I prefer messaging me though craigslist before giving out numbers.",,fair,other,rwd,gas,,silver,compact,clean,other,

Here I have a 1988 Toyota MR2 NA, that means it's not supercharged, with around 187,000 miles. It is a 5 speed manual. There are alot of new parts on the motor and chassis and I will get to those in a list down below.

The paint is nowhere near excellent, maybe good or fair condition, but this is a rare color and even being a two tone makes in even more rare. THERE ARE NO LEAKS, all the rubber seals are holding all the water on the outside of the car, as they should. column1: https://carbondale.craigslist.org/cto/d/1989-mercedes-benz-sl-560/6625630274.html,1989 Mercedes Benz SL 560,1989 mercedes benz,Neoga,6500,Car was purchased locally and has been in a storage unit since 2011. This is an older restore car with documentation. Car runs good with no engine lights on. Paint shines nice but has small rock chips etc nothing bad. Interior is all there and not bad for a 28 yr old car but certainly not perfect.  Soft top is all there but vinyl not in good shape. Will need new floor pans in rear as the soft top leaked at some point . They are fairly inexpensive to replace.  Car shows 192k but speedometer quit working 2 months before it was parked according to previous owner. Car is a running driving project but would not take much to be a very nice car. Has had recent new exhaust work done and brakes etc are all good. Prices on these car have been steadily rising so great opportunity to get into one cheap. Priced below value to compensate for the few problems stated above. Can get more pics for those of you interested. Text or call with questions.,,,,,gas,,,,clean,automatic,
